@DESCRIPTION: Marketing Strategy Management sub-domain groups functions useful to define the marketstrategy (existing and desired market-place, activities and aims, objectives to be achieved, market segmentation) and to develop market, channels.
Marketing Strategic Analysis sub-domain groups functions useful to conduct delayed analysis, on the collected information concerning market, which may have an influence on the strategy.

Marketing Campaign Development sub-domain groups operational functions useful to define campaigns. There are different campaigns types, direct marketing campaigns, but also information campaigns (by examples information about the migrations, newsletters, …).
Sales Commission Management sub-domain groups functions specifying commission rules for the Service Provider's employees such as Sales Agent.
Marketing Campaign Management sub-domain groups operational functions useful to conduct campaign. …).

The Sales Commissioning Management sub-function encompasses several functionalities:
• the definition of commissioning rules for the sellers, dealers or resellers
• commissions calcul for sellers, dealers or resellers from information such as orders, activation, usage ... applying commission rules
The Presales sub-domain includes functions which concern the prospective customer relationship.
Sales Management sub-domain groups functions in charge of processing the proposition, negotiation and sales towards a customer interested in an offer or product.

Product Analysis sub-domain groups functions useful to conduct delayed analysis, on the collected information concerning products such as product usages or product usages, which may have an influence on the strategy.

@NAME: Product Specification & Offering Strategy Definition & Analysis
@DESCRIPTION: Product Specification & Offering Strategy Definition & Analysis defines the overall structure of the offers and products portfolios to be used across the enterprise. It is established, from the Offer and Product analysis, in respect with the strategic business direction and covers new offers and products as well as existing offers and products. This sub-domain also groups functions related to Product Specification & Offering Strategy Analysis conduct.

The Product Specification & Offering Management Sub-Domain Functions enable to create and update the catalogue. This function covers the impact on the offer and product catalogue of new offers and products launches, modifications and withdrawals. This function manages the lifecycle of offers and products and includes the various possibilities of offer or product search and browse (wizard, multicriterion search, category browse…).
Product Repository Management sub-domain groups functions in charge of managing the inventory of installed Products corresponding as well to ProductSpecification or ProductOffering.
Product Performance Management sub-domain groups functions in charge of assuring that SLA agreements made between operators and customers are met.
Product Problem Management sub-domain groups functions responsible for the management of a problem concerning a product.

The Product Usage Management sub-domain functions aim at:
• identify the product(s) concerned by every relevant Service Usage Records (for example CDR) and to produce Product Usage Record(s).
• filter the Service Usage Records that have no interest for rating or reporting.
The Rating and Follow Up sub-domain groups functions related to rating and to consumption follow up activities.
Customer Strategic Analysis sub-domain groups functions useful to conduct delayed analysis, on the collected information concerning market and customer, which may have an influence on the strategy.
Customer Information Specification Management sub-domain functions is in charge of specifying information and its calculation rules for Customer Information that needs to be calculated.
Customer Information Support sub-domain functions groups functions in charge of collecting, qualifying and managing Customer information and also personalizing Customer profile.

Customer Order Management functions manage the end to end lifecycle of a Customer Order request from the establishment to the complete delivery. This includes Customer Order Establishment, Customer Order Tracking and LifeCycle Management, as well as Customer Order Orchestration.
Customer Problem Support sub-domain contains functions responsible for the management of customer request concerning problem, assistance or information.
Customer Financial Management sub-domain groups functions which manage the processing of financial transactions affecting the customer's financial account.
The Invoice Management sub-domain groups functions related to the production of the customer invoices and to prevention activities.
Customer Loyalty and Retention sub-domain groups functions related to the use of loyalty schemes to attract and gain the loyalty of customers, and to the retention of acquired customers.

Customer Management Support sub-domain groups functions to collect, qualify and manage customer information and personalize customer profile.
Note: The term “Customer” is used in the broad sense: it represents here person or organisation, potential, existing or former customer and even product user, buyer...
Welcome and Interaction sub-domain groups functions in charge of managing all interfaces between the company and the existing or prospective customer.
Service Strategy Management sub-domain groups functions useful to define the service strategy and to develop it (new services or enhance the existing services).
Service Capability Management sub-domain functions groups functions in charge of specifying and managing ServiceSpecification capabilities.
Service Test Capability Management sub-domain functions groups functions in charge of checking availability of all what is needed to implement Service tests.
The Service Quality and Performance Management sub-domain groups functions that supervise service functioning and manage resulting alarms.

The Service Specification Development sub-domain functions enable to create and update the catalogue at Service level :
• definition of the Service Provider’s know-hows (CustomerFacingServices specification) and pre-requisite
• definition of the technical solutions available for each know-how (ResourceFacingServicesspecification)
• links with the Supplier Product Catalogue for know-hows, technical solutions or part of technical solutions not realized by the Service Provider itself.
It is also responsible for implementing the service strategy high level plan and develop the service infrastructure that will be used to provide the service (through products) to the customers at large (mass market, enterprise, to third parties/partners...) The Service Deployment and Retirement function manages the deployment constraints like area limitation (for test or for marketing purposes), progressive deployment following precise milestones…

Service Test Specification Development sub-domain functions provide the necessary functionalities to manage the service test catalogue containing the service test specifications, the rules that define the test configuration setting up based on the context, the rules that define the strategies for executing the test as well as how the test results should be restituted.
Test strategies can range from simple to complex and encompass the definition of test scenario.
The definition of the test (with specification and rules) is very important because it defines the question that is asked and thus shapes the result that is reported back.
The functionalities include providing:
• Service Test Specification and test scenario management
  - Test scenario management: for example, a home equipment self-test can trigger a test scenario that verifies the functioning of all the services associated, depending on the installed products of the user. Thus, the Box could test its internal configuration and functioning and its capacity to connect to internet and VoIP services.
  - Managing service test capabilities: some resources used to implement services have limited capabilities for executing tests, especially for multiple parallel testing. All the constraints linked to limited resources test capabilities and depending on the execution context must be aggregated and managed at service test level.
  - Managing initiator authorization: some tests are restricted to some user roles (internal or external) so the authorization are defined at the Service Test Strategy and Policy Management
• Test rules defining the strategies for setting up test configuration
• Test rules defining how to carrying out the service test
  - For example: to choose the next test in a scenario depending on the results of the previous tests
• Test rules defining the enrichment of test results. 
  - For example: enrichment of internet bandwidth measure based on installed product
• Test rules defining the restitution of the result depending on test execution context
   - For example: a test result of ok/not ok can be enough for a user whereas customer care requires more details in the result of the test.
Service Management groups functions in charge of managing the inventory of installed services.

Service Test Management sub-domain functions provide the necessary functionalities to manage the end-to-end execution of a test for a service (test of a service use case getting through all concerned resources, local loop, DSLAM, Service Platform, …), either for manual or automatic testing in order to ensure that this service is working properly.
Service Order Management (SOM) functions manage the end to end lifecycle of a Service Order request, from its configuration up to the technical delivery on network equipment and service platforms.
Service Problem Management groups functions in charge of managing Service Trouble.
The Service Quality and Performance Management sub-domain groups functions that supervise service functioning and manage resulting alarms.
Resource Strategic Analysis sub-domain groups functions useful to conduct delayed analysis, on the collected information concerning resource, which may have an influence on the strategy.
Resource Strategy Management sub-domain groups functions useful to define the resource strategy and to develop it (new resources or enhance the existing resources).
Resource Capability Management sub-domain functions groups functions in charge of specifying and managing ResourceSpecification capabilities.

The Resource Specification Management sub-domain functions enable to create and update the catalogue at Resource level, for all types of resources (ResourceSpecification):
• Physical Resources (ex: cable, passive equipment, …)
• Logical Resources (ex: phone number, IP address, APPS such as Orange TV, Orange Maps, …)
• Compound Resources (ex: DSLAM, box, …)
It manages the links with the Business Partner Product Catalogue for Resources specification that correspond to equipment rented to a supplier (devices, network equipment, hardware & software, …).
It also manages the links to the Skill catalogue to identify for each type of resource – or of operation on a resource – which type of skill is necessary to make the intervention.
Work Order Development sub-domain functions groups functions in charge of Work specifications development.
Resource Management groups functions in charge of managing the inventory of resources.

Resource Test Management provides the necessary functionalities to manage the end-to-end execution of a test for a resource, either for manual or automatic testing in order to ensure that this resource is working properly. It includes:
• Verifying test authorization and quota management
• Carrying out test priority
• Managing test scheduling
• Managing bulk test
• Retrieval of appropriate inventory data and setting up the test context and configuration
• Test execution with access to the various resources required to perform resource testing
• Managing resource test scenario
• Test results restitution
• Test results long term logging for offline data analyses. 
• Possible reporting of test results back to the initiator of the test.

The Work Order Management sub-domain functions track and manage the events and the lifecycle related to Work Orders, and assures that they are assigned, coordinated and escalating as needed.
 It is especially in charge of initiating re-assignments as needed, based on changing priorities, technician progress on other job assignments, etc.
Resource Order Management functions manage the end to end lifecycle of a Resource Order request.
Supply Chain Fulfillment sub-domain groups functions related to stock movement, logistics, inventory control, assembling process.
The Resource Performance Management sub-domain groups functions that supervise resource functioning and manage resulting alarms.

The Resource Usage Management sub-domain functions consist in follow-up of the Resource use, based on Resource. It deals with reports and analysis with an on-the-fly analysis (detailed & aggregated) of the resource uses and comparison with the resource capacity management and with the resource usage analysis forecasts.
Business Partner Strategy Analysis sub-domain groups functions that manage analysis from Business Partners such as risk analysis.
Purchasing Strategy Analysis sub-domain functions groups functions in charge of analysing purchasing application and sourcing savings.
Purchasing Strategy Management sub-domain functions groups functions in charge of defining Purchasing Strategy, Purchasing needs forecast and purchasing request management.

@NAME: Business Partner Product Specification and Offering Management
@DESCRIPTION: Business Partner Product Specification and Offering Management sub-domain groups functions that manage Business Partner's Product Specification and Offering onboarding and request for quotation.

The Business Partner Management sub-domain functions enable the creation and updates of Business Partner information such as name, address, organisation, site location, interlocutors and interlocutor roles (legal representative…). 
The term “Business Partner” is used in the broad sense: dealer, reseller, wholesales, content provider (e.g. TV on XDSL), other network operator for interconnection or roaming purpose, Logistic Operator, partner, service provider for the technical support and IT projects, …
When the CSP decides to work with a Business Partner, he is referenced and typified (Supplier or Supplier and Partner, or with regard to the contents of purchases). 
It also manages supplier lists, preferred suppliers lists and also suppliers' black list, with information such as name, address…
Business Partner Order Management sub-domain groups functions that manage the order to supplier or partner and the control of their fulfillment.
The Business Partner Performance Management sub-domain groups functions used to evaluate Business Partners performance such as Supplier Performance.
The Business Partner Financial Management sub-domain groups functions used to pay Business Partners.
Business Partner Invoice Management sub-domain groups functions which manage the financial interface with the supplier or partner including invoice matching and settlement.
Business Partner Rating sub-domain groups functions which manage the rating part of the supplier or partner.
Business Partner Welcome and Interaction sub-domain groups functions in charge of managing all interfaces between the company and Business Partners.
Financial Management sub-domain contains functions that permit budget, treasury as well as employee expenses management.
This sub-domain groups functions which manage the teams operational detailed workload schedule.
Bank Management sub-domain functions is in charge of managing CSP's Bank Accounts.
The Revenue Assurance Management sub-domain includes functions which are in charge of defining company strategy and methods to minimize the revenue leakage.
Human Resource Assurance sub-domain functions groups functions in charge of defining, analyzing and reporting short and long terms goals for employees.
Accounting Management sub-domain contains functions which allow to manage the accounting of the company.
Human Resource Expense Management sub-domain functions cover the treatment of employee’s expenses such as payroll and travel expenses.

The Asset Management sub-domain mainly permits to:
• manage all the resources which are used and shared within the company, namely the physical and financial assets deployed in the enterprise
• optimize the expected savings linked to these all along their lifecycle from their purchase and setup until their total depreciation or amortization.

This sub-domain embeds three functions:
• Corporate Real Estate Management
• Vehicle Fleet Management
• Intellectual Property Management

This sub-domain DOESN'T manage the Tangible and Intangible Products sold to the CUSTOMERS, only those used within the enterprise for its own needs.
Employee Management sub-domain functions groups functions in charge of managing the Employee Inventory and employee relationship management.
Enterprise Information Management sub-domain functions groups functions in charge of managing all knowledge of the Enterprise.
Enterprise Risk Management sub-domain functions groups functions in charge of managing Enterprise Ricks realizing audits, managing patent, invention and damage claims.

@NAME: Human Resource Administration, Compensation and Benefits Management
@DESCRIPTION:
The Human Resource Administration, Compensation and Benefits Management sub-domain groups functions in charge of
1. processing and managing records and employee’s data, ensuring they are accurate and up-to-date, corresponding and taking into account any changes resulting from management decisions, legal and regulatory requirements and personal circumstances,
2. managing the individual Compensation and Benefits calculation, giving the instructions for the payroll process.
Note that for some countries (UK), the Information System must provide functions for pension funds and social security management.

Human Resource Human Capital Management sub-domain groups functions covering all the operations and data related to human resource and competencies development.
It covers, on one hand, the internal and external processes of recruitment, and, on the other hand, the processes contributing in the management of the performance and competencies which aims to improve individual performance and, by this way, to insure the achievement of Orange group's strategic business goals.

Human Resource Social Management sub-domain groups functions covering all the operations and data related to social management.
It defines the policy for employee’s relations, health and safety, and corporate social responsibility. It supports managers in their implementation and control results.
Each company / country develops its own approach in employee’s relations, health and safety, work time and corporate social responsibility in coherence with group policies and local legal and mandatory requirements and agreements.

Regulatory Rules Management sub-domain functions groups functions in charge of managing regulatory rules, checking their application by the enterprise and providing reporting of regulatory rules to various legal and regulatory entities.
The Security Management sub-domain includes functions in charge of defining company strategy and means to improve security.
The Privacy Development sub-domain functions are in charge of specifying Privacy Rules to be applied.
The Privacy Management sub-domain functions are in charge of applying the Privacy Rules when required.
The Content Management sub-domain allows documents and contents management, sharing and archiving.
The Master Data Management sub-domain gathers all required functions for enterprise master data administration. It aims at unifying data repositories management whatever the business domain.
The Project Management sub-domain contains functions concerning the management of all kinds of projects.

The Identification and Permission Management sub-domain functions consist in 
   - identifying, and potentially authenticating, a person whatever his/her role(s),
   - specifying roles and permissions definition, assignment and control for any actor implicated in the enterprise business processes (ex: customer, CSR, data protection manager, Business Partners …).
